            NAME            NAME
            make.barscale - Generates from one to four bar scale units,
            as a single map element, on the map composition.
            
            SYNOPSIS            SYNOPSIS
            make.barscale [filename]            make.barscale                                      ________ 
            
            DESCRIPTION            DESCRIPTION
            make.barscale constructs from one to four bar scales on the            _____________                                              
            map composition as a single map element.  The user designs
            the bar scale(s) by responding to a series of questions
            regarding the measuring units (i.e. feet, miles, kilometers,
            and/or meters), the number of units to the right of the zero
            point, position location, and the text font and size.  The
            vertical height of the bar scale will be generated at
            approximately three times the height of the text.  If given,
            [filename] is used for the name of the overlay file             ________                                          
            generated.
            
            The user is required to provide the following:
            
                 - map definition file name
                 - overlay file name (if not specified on the command
                      line)
                 - plotter pen number
                 - text font
                 - text size
                 - text leading
                 - relationship of the bar scale to a window
                      within the map composition
                 - location for the center of the barscale(s)
                 - measuring units
                 - measuring units per bar scale unit (i.e. miles per
                      unit)
                 - number of bar scale units to the right of zero
                 - number of divisions in unit to the left of zero
            
            Completing the response sequence generates the required
            files to construct the map element.  Definition parameters
            are stored in the misc directory; graphic elements to draw                              ____                                    
            the map on the screen or plotter are stored in the ovm                                                               ___
            directory.  The default file name for both directories is
            barscale.            ________ 
            
            Changing the appearance of the bar scale (e.g. position,
            text size, measuring units, etc.) can be done by
            regenerating the make.barscale command and overwriting the                             _____________                            
            initial file, or by editing the text definition file, then
            executing it directly, or by using the redo.misc command.                                                   _________         

            
