            Information entered through the interactive make.barscale                                                        _____________
            command has been reformatted to meet the requirements of the
            MAPGEN command legend, prefacing the element characteristics                           ______                                       
            with options for the legend command.  All options available                                 ______                                
            in the legend command are available for use in the GRASS-                   ______                                            
            MAPGEN Interface.  Commonly used legend options associated                                             ______                   
            with making bar scale(s) are:
                 
                 -w (window/region) [data=d][map plot=p]                                          _           _ 
                 -f (style) [font=-alphanumeric]                                  _____________ 
                 -p (pen) [plotter pen location=value]                                                _____ 
                 -s (size) [centimeter=value]                                       _____ 
                 -j (justify) [center=c][right=r][left=l]                                      _        _       _ 
                 -x (horizontal coordinate) [right=>[centimeter=value]]                                                   _            _____  
                                          [left=<[centimeter=value]]                                                _            _____  
                                          [center=|[centimeter=value]]                                                  _            _____  
                 -y (vertical coordinate) [top=>[centimeter=value]]                                               _            _____  
                                        [bottom=<[centimeter=value]]                                                _            _____  
                                        [center=|[centimeter=value]]                                                _            _____  
                 -b (bar) [size,unit,rep[,left[,right]]                           _____________ _____ ______  
                 -d (scale display)
            
            EXAMPLE            EXAMPLE
            The file misc/barscale will draw three stacked bar scale                     _____________                                  
            units, one each for miles, feet and kilometers,
            respectively.  The text size displayed on the bar scales is
            0.15 cm tall and drawn with pen in position 1 on the
            plotter.  The one mile bar scale has 10 divisions to the
            left of the zero, and 1 to the right; the feet bar scale has
            7 divisions to the right of the zero (i.e. 7000 feet), and 2
            to the left; and the one kilometer bar scale has 10
            divisions to the left of the zero, and 1 to the right.  The
            representative fraction (RF) is printed, centered above the
            bar scales.
            
                 legend -m map.def -o ovm/barscale << EOF
                 -w d
                 -p 1
                 -f -
                 -s 0.150
                 -x |
                 -y -1.50
                 -b 1,mi,1,10,MILE
                 -x |-3.8
                 -y -2.160
                 -b 1000,ft,7,2,FEET
                 -x |

            
